    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-04-17T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-04-17T04:00:00-05:00" n="42"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d42">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">883.927/109: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Howell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-04-17T11:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 17, 1926—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 17—8:54 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>15. Department’s telegram No. 9, April 12.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>(1)</label>
                    <item>The political situation is now favorable to making representations which
                        in my judgment and that of Mr. Winlock will be satisfactory to the
                        Metropolitan interests.</item>
                    <label>(2)</label>
                    <item>Department’s note is objectionable in several days: (<hi rend="italic"
                            >a</hi>) It contains superfluous history and belabors the real points at
                        issue; (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) it is objectionable to Doctor
                        Reisner.</item>
                    <pb facs="0168" n="72" xml:id="pg_72"/>
                    <label>(3)</label>
                    <item>Reisner approves <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> in which I request
                        Egyptian Government or Ministry under which Lacau works to approve
                        officially Lacau’s interpretation of the spirit of article 10 as expressed
                        in the circular letters which he has sent to the various expeditions.</item>
                    <label>(4)</label>
                    <item>The language to be used by Egyptian Government in the separate articles to
                        be issued to concessionaires will embody the principles set forth in
                        Department’s note. British [and French?] support this proposition.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Howell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
